<!-- Applying Colors and Backgrounds in CSS
In CSS, colors can be defined using various formats:

Hexadecimal (#RRGGBB): A six-character code representing red, green, and blue values.
RGB (rgb(r, g, b)): Specifies the red, green, and blue values between 0â€“255.
HSL (hsl(hue, saturation%, lightness%)): A color model based on hue, saturation, and lightness. -->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Colors and Backgrounds in CSS</title>

    <style>
        /* Body with a solid color background */
        body {
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            /* Light gray using Hex */
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        /* Header with a linear gradient background */
        header {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #ff7e5f, #feb47b);
            /* Gradient from left to right */
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px 0;
        }

        /* Section with an RGB background */
        section {
            background-color: rgb(173, 216, 230);
            /* Light blue using RGB */
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        /* Article with an HSL background */
        article {
            background-color: hsl(120, 60%, 70%);
            /* Light green using HSL */
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        /* Footer with a background image */
        footer {
            background-image: url('background.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            /* Ensures the image covers the entire area */
            background-position: center;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Color and Background Demo</h1>
        <p>Using gradients, RGB, HSL, and images in CSS</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Section with RGB Background</h2>
        <p>This section uses a background color defined with the RGB model.</p>
    </section>

    <article>
        <h2>Article with HSL Background</h2>
        <p>This article uses a background color defined with the HSL model.</p>
    </article>

    <footer>
        <p>Footer with Background Image</p>
    </footer>

</body>

</html>

<!-- Summary
This example demonstrates:

Solid colors with different formats: Hex, RGB, and HSL.
Gradient backgrounds for smooth transitions between colors.
Image backgrounds with proper scaling and positioning. -->